Example of using CreDating

Xavier Didelot

2017-11-07

Initialisation

library(CreDating)
library(ape)
set.seed(0)

Data

We start by generating a random timed tree with 20 leaves and root in 2000:

phy <- simdatedtree(nsam = 20, dateroot = 2000)
plot(phy)
axisPhylo(backward = F)

We can extract the sampling dates as follows:

dates = leafDates(phy)
#dates[seq(2,20,2)]=NA#Oops, just lost half of the dates!
#dates[1]=NA#Oops, just lost a date!

On each branch we observe a number of substitutions which is distributed \(\mathrm{Gamma}(rl,1)\) where \(l\) is the branch length and \(r=10\) per year is the substitution rate. We can simulate an observed phylogenetic tree and perform a root-to-tip analysis as follows:

obsphy=simobsphy(phy, rate=10,model='gamma')
res=roottotip(obsphy,dates,predInt='gamma',showTree=T)

Unknown root

Lets say we dont know where the root is:

obsphy=unroot(obsphy)

Analysis

We run CreDating as follows:

res=credate(obsphy,dates,nbIts = 10000,model='gamma',updateRoot = 2,showProgress=T)

plot(res)

Plot with credibility bars:

plot(res,'treeCI')

We can see what the MCMC traces look like:

plot(res,'trace')

Lets see where the root is likely to be:

plot(res,'treeRoot')
